{
  "_README": [
    "TEMPLATE for services/wxmonitor/appsettings.local.json (the REAL file is gitignored).",
    "Copy this file to 'appsettings.local.json' in THIS folder and fill the <...> placeholders",
    "(the SQL password lives in RoboForm). docker-compose.yml bind-mounts the real file READ-ONLY",
    "into the container at /opt/wxservices/appsettings.local.json.",
    "",
    "The service loads appsettings.shared.json (baked into the image) FIRST, then this file on",
    "top, last-value-wins. So this carries ONLY the keys that must DIFFER for a container: the",
    "database doorway (+ SQL login) and the telemetry endpoint. Everything else - SMTP host/port,",
    "Monitor thresholds, watched services - comes from shared. SMTP username/password/from-address",
    "are read from the GlobalSettings database row, NOT from here.",
    "",
    "Keys beginning with underscore are documentation; the .NET config binder ignores them."
  ],

  "ConnectionStrings": {
    "_README": [
      "Container override. Reach the host's SQL Server via host.docker.internal,1433 (proven in",
      "WX-67) instead of the shared config's Server=.\\SQLEXPRESS. Use SQL authentication with the",
      "'wxservices' login - scoped to db_owner on WeatherData ONLY (the minimum for the",
      "migrate-on-startup design: EnsureSchemaAsync runs MigrateAsync, which needs DDL rights; no",
      "server-wide or other-database access). A Linux container has no Windows identity, so",
      "Trusted_Connection can't work here."
    ],
    "WeatherData": "Server=host.docker.internal,1433;Database=WeatherData;User Id=wxservices;Password=<WXSERVICES_SQL_PASSWORD>;TrustServerCertificate=True;"
  },

  "Telemetry": {
    "_README": [
      "Container override. The OTel collector is reached at the host's PUBLISHED 4318 port; the",
      "shared config's http://localhost:4318 would resolve to the container itself. Include the",
      "full signal path (/v1/metrics). Enabled is set explicitly here (shared config also sets it",
      "true) so a copied config can't silently disable metrics - AddWxTelemetry exports only when true."
    ],
    "Enabled": true,
    "OtlpEndpoint": "http://host.docker.internal:4318/v1/metrics"
  },

  "Monitor": {
    "_README": [
      "OPTIONAL. Shared config already sets AlertEmail, thresholds, and WatchedServices, so most",
      "deployments need nothing here. Set the two Grafana keys ONLY if THIS container should also",
      "run the WX-279 zero-dashboard detector: point GrafanaUrl at the host's published grafana",
      "(http://host.docker.internal:3000) and paste the Viewer service-account token (RoboForm).",
      "Leave GrafanaUrl empty to keep that detector dormant."
    ],
    "GrafanaUrl": "",
    "GrafanaServiceAccountToken": ""
  }
}
